Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.98,0:00:03.60,Default,Girl1,0,0,0,,Did you hear about Ayano?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.60,0:00:07.11,Default,Girl2,0,0,0,,She tried to escape, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.11,0:00:07.86,Default,Girl1,0,0,0,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.86,0:00:10.52,Default,Girl3,0,0,0,,Did she die because \Nshe tried escaping?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.52,0:00:11.32,Default,Girl1,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.85,0:00:16.57,Default,Girl2,0,0,0,,Ogura's brother died \Nthat day too, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.57,0:00:17.57,Default,Girl1,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.57,0:00:19.65,Default,Girl3,0,0,0,,Wasn't he a shut-in?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.65,0:00:20.20,Default,Girl2,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.68,0:00:24.25,Default,Girl1,0,0,0,,I heard something \Nabout the class trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.25,0:00:26.13,Default,Girl1,0,0,0,,Get this, apparently \Nit's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.13,0:00:27.25,Default,Girl2,0,0,0,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.25,0:00:30.00,Default,Girl3,0,0,0,,Like, asking the gods for help?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.00,0:00:32.29,Default,Girl1,0,0,0,,I heard the class was \Nsaved before by doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.61,0:00:35.63,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Stupid...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.04,0:00:39.13,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Stupid brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.67,0:00:42.05,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.27,0:00:45.17,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.89,0:00:48.73,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I'm sorry! Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.20,0:00:57.37,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.83,0:01:02.53,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you. \NI'm Sakakibara Kouichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.92,0:01:16.92,Sign,Kanji Title,0,0,0,,{\an8\b0\fscx100\fs40\fsp1\c&HF2F2F2&\blur0.6\pos(1075.5,564)}Jet Black
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.92,0:01:26.93,Sign,Sign,0,0,0,,{\an8\c&H16313F&\fnSquickt\fs24\3c&H729FBD&\bord3\blur2\pos(1048,157)}Sakitani\NMemorial\NHall
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.23,0:01:21.37,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Got the tape?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.37,0:01:22.82,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.82,0:01:23.77,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Listen to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.77,0:01:24.81,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.81,0:01:26.93,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,I'm too scared to do it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.19,0:01:42.15,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Let's take a commemoration photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.15,0:01:44.78,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,It's our last summer \Nbreak in junior high.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.78,0:01:46.28,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.04,0:01:49.93,Default,Sign,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnSquickt\fs32\bord3\blur2\c&H10191F&\frz46.089\pos(685,45)\3c&H254958&}Sakitani\NMemorial Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.04,0:01:49.91,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Everyone line up over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.81,0:01:54.92,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.92,0:01:56.79,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Let's get the teachers in it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.43,0:02:01.32,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,All right, almost ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.03,0:02:05.33,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Sakakibara and Misaki, \Nsqueeze a little closer together.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.44,0:02:14.59,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Mochizuki, you \Nshould be in one too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.59,0:02:15.86,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,I'll take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.14,0:02:18.48,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.59,0:02:22.59,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Hey, Mochizuki, you and \NMs. Mikami are too spread out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.59,0:02:24.78,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,You too, Sakaki and Misaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.78,0:02:26.20,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Kazami, you're fine there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.42,0:02:29.99,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,All right. Say, "Cheese"!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.51,0:02:38.39,Default,Mikami,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, we'll visit the \Nshrine to pray for our safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.39,0:02:39.50,Default,All,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.36,0:02:42.58,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,This is a nice lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.58,0:02:46.64,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,A local business donated \Nits recreation center.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.64,0:02:51.17,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,A bit lavish for \Nstudents, if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.17,0:02:53.64,Default,Numata,0,0,0,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.64,0:02:56.23,Default,Numata,0,0,0,,We've kept all the \Nrooms open for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.23,0:02:59.44,Default,Mikami,0,0,0,,Thank you for having us \Nfor the next three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.44,0:03:01.11,Default,Numata,0,0,0,,We're happy to. \NThanks for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.11,0:03:04.99,Default,Numata,0,0,0,,If you need anything, \Ndon't hesitate to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.60,0:03:11.79,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.25,0:03:14.64,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.62,0:03:25.56,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}—Now, this is the important part.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.56,0:03:29.88,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}It happened after we reached \Nthe bottom of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.88,0:03:33.27,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}And by{\fsp5} {\fsp0\i0}it{\i1}, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.01,0:03:34.98,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.98,0:03:38.89,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}It happened in the forest, \Noutside of the lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.89,0:03:42.57,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I got into an argument \Nwith a guy named—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.57,0:03:46.06,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}We went at each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.06,0:03:48.57,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}And... And...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.02,0:03:53.08,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}...before I realized it, \Nhe wasn't moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.45,0:03:57.15,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}He was lying \Nunder a huge tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.15,0:04:01.09,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}When I took a closer look, \NI noticed he'd been impaled by a branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.63,0:04:04.51,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}—was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.51,0:04:09.51,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I was terrified, so I ran back \Nto my room at the lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.51,0:04:13.64,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}They decided that we were \Ngoing to stay for another night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.64,0:04:16.54,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}The police also came to see us \Nabout the lightning and the fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.54,0:04:18.98,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}They asked me \Na lot of questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.98,0:04:23.02,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}but I couldn't \Ntell them about—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.80,0:04:26.15,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I hardly slept that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.46,0:04:32.53,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Surely everyone would freak out if they found the body of—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.95,0:04:37.41,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Come morning, it was evident that no one had found out,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.41,0:04:42.41,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}so I went back into the \Nforest to take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.41,0:04:45.67,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}But... it wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.67,0:04:49.66,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}It had vanished \Nwithout a trace.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.66,0:04:52.39,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I was baffled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.60,0:04:57.09,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I went to ask everyone \Nwhat had happened to—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.09,0:04:59.98,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}But they just looked \Nat me like I was crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.34,0:05:04.82,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}They said, "Who's that?" and, \N"I don't know anyone named that."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.52,0:05:11.24,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}They even said there were 19 \Nstudents on the trip, not 20.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.78,0:05:14.87,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's when it dawned on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.87,0:05:24.08,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}The guy I killed must have \Nbeen the extra student. {alt. I must've killed the extra student.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.73,0:05:28.30,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I knew without \Na doubt that I killed—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.01,0:05:31.22,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nothing can change that fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.22,0:05:34.56,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's why I decided \Nto come clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.17,0:05:38.22,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is my confession.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.71,0:05:40.58,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's been two weeks \Nsince that trip,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.58,0:05:45.73,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}and only I, the person involved \Nwith his death, can still remember—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.73,0:05:49.77,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I get the feeling it's only \Na matter of time, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.77,0:05:53.04,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's why, while I \Ncan still remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.04,0:05:54.74,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I want to tell you the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.74,0:05:58.87,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}and how you can \Nstop the calamity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.79,0:06:01.07,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.07,0:06:03.04,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Send them back to death, \Nwhere they belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.75,0:06:05.85,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Send the dead back to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.52,0:06:10.99,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's how to stop the \Ncalamity once it's begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.57,0:06:22.27,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I couldn't make out his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.84,0:06:26.65,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Does that mean \Nthis has been altered?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.08,0:06:28.13,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.08,0:06:31.40,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,It must be real, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.83,0:06:35.53,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,There's no reason \Nto alter a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.82,0:06:42.24,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Well, we don't need the name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.24,0:06:44.00,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,What matters is how \Nwe stop the calamity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.00,0:06:47.89,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,They say there's no way to \Ntell the dead from the living,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.72,0:06:50.75,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,and that they don't \Nknow they're dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.75,0:06:53.00,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Is there any way to tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.00,0:06:54.65,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,There doesn't seem to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.65,0:06:57.64,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Mr. Matsunaga's case \Nwas pure coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.76,0:07:04.52,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,You don't think the extra student \Nis here, at this lodge, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.99,0:07:12.93,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Say we do figure out who it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.50,0:07:15.48,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.48,0:07:17.99,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Are we supposed to... kill them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.99,0:07:19.12,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Well—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.12,0:07:21.74,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Could you kill a classmate?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.74,0:07:43.26,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,You know, I've been thinking \Nabout who the extra person could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.92,0:07:45.53,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Do you have someone in mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.53,0:07:46.71,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.53,0:07:54.15,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,I just think there must be \Nsome way to tell who it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.15,0:07:56.90,Sign,Text,0,0,0,,{\an7\p1\pos(631,321)\fscx100\fscy99\c&HCBDADC&}m -64 -76 l 152 -4 120 38 71 61 56 80 61 79 110 55 76 102 15 77 10 29 8 40 10 75 -132 26 -120 16 -146 21 -152 19{\p0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.15,0:07:56.90,Sign,Text,0,0,0,,{\an5\c&H49408A&\fnPT Sans\fs49\fsp2\fay-0.12\fax-0.1\frx30\frz329.553\pos(629,335)}Keep inhaler \N{\fsp2\fax-0.05\fay-0.125}in bag when\h \N{\fsp6\fscx93\fay-0.14\fax-0.1}not in use.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.64,0:07:56.90,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Maybe there is, and we \Njust don't know about it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.52,0:07:58.80,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.69,0:08:04.70,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,May I have a moment, \NMs. Mikami?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.42,0:08:09.46,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Since we're all together, \Nthere's something I'd like to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.46,0:08:11.12,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Is that all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.90,0:08:13.96,Default,Mikami,0,0,0,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.96,0:08:15.86,Default,Mikami,0,0,0,,Go ahead, Akazawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.25,0:08:26.37,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Since May, we've experienced \Nnothing but misfortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.37,0:08:30.40,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Just last month, even \NMr. Kubodera became a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.14,0:08:36.19,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,For starters, I'd like to apologize for my \Nincompetence as the head of countermeasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.24,0:08:44.35,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Additionally, though it remains unclear whether or not this trip leads us toward a resolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.97,0:08:52.46,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I sincerely believe that you, Misaki, \Nhold some of the responsibility for these disasters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.43,0:08:55.25,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.25,0:08:55.30,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.99,0:09:01.79,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I believe if Misaki had upheld her \Nrole as the nonexistent student properly,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.79,0:09:03.51,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,then no one would have died.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.51,0:09:05.26,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.26,0:09:07.42,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,What happened was unavoidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.42,0:09:09.02,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,She couldn't do anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.02,0:09:10.44,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.44,0:09:16.08,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,If she had avoided all \Ncontact with Sakakibara,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.08,0:09:17.65,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,then the countermeasure \Nwould have been a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.65,0:09:18.02,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,But—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.02,0:09:22.20,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I believe the person responsible \Nfor its failure is Misaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.20,0:09:22.87,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Wouldn't you all agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.86,0:09:25.62,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,What do you expect \Nher to do about it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.80,0:09:30.75,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.13,0:09:35.25,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,We have yet to hear one \Nword of apology from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.69,0:09:39.13,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Yet, the moment you \Nwere allowed to exist again,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.13,0:09:41.80,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,you carried on as if \Nnothing had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.80,0:09:43.64,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It's pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.51,0:09:47.78,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Apologizing changes nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.53,0:09:49.98,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,If you believe so, then I shall.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.33,0:09:59.56,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Misaki, you have \Nnothing to apologize for.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.33,0:10:03.90,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.90,0:10:05.03,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.03,0:10:05.87,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,It's not!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.87,0:10:06.53,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.28,0:10:08.63,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,This is stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.63,0:10:11.87,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,We just need to figure \Nout who the extra st—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.87,0:10:13.88,Default,Kazami,0,0,0,,Hey, Wakui, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.35,0:10:20.51,Default,Maejima,0,0,0,,Are you in pain?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.51,0:10:21.57,Default,Kazami,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.80,0:10:25.69,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Is this boy asthmatic?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.69,0:10:28.23,Default,Kazami,0,0,0,,Yes. He always carries this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.10,0:10:32.25,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,An inhaler? \NShouldn't he use this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.77,0:10:34.42,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,It's empty?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.42,0:10:35.02,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Do you have a spare?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.65,0:10:41.40,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Call an ambulance! \NMs. Mikami, call an ambulance now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.40,0:10:42.11,Default,Numata,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.55,0:10:46.44,Default,Numata,0,0,0,,Our phones haven't been working \Nsince yesterday. We can't make any calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.44,0:10:48.03,Default,Numata,0,0,0,,We've arranged for repairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.64,0:10:48.03,Alternative,Chibiki,0,0,0,,It's out of range.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.03,0:10:49.79,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Does anyone have service?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.79,0:10:52.47,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Call 119! Get an \Nambulance over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.47,0:10:54.56,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,It says there's an antenna \Nhere, but I can't connect!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.56,0:10:56.04,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Mine won't work, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.04,0:10:57.28,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,There's no service.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.87,0:11:00.05,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,I'll drive him to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.35,0:11:20.90,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.09,0:11:25.71,Default,Mikami,0,0,0,,I'm not the one you \Nshould be worried about.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.71,0:11:29.52,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Maybe we shouldn't go up \Nthe mountain tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.52,0:11:31.37,Default,Mikami,0,0,0,,Maybe not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.64,0:11:38.19,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Sakakibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.83,0:11:40.24,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.24,0:11:42.01,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Thanks for earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.01,0:11:43.07,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.07,0:11:46.17,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,You stood up for me \Nin the dining room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.17,0:11:49.05,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Oh. It was nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.54,0:11:51.47,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,It wasn't just me, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.47,0:11:53.77,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,There was Mochizuki \Nand Teshigawara too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.77,0:11:54.94,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.56,0:12:00.37,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Will you come see me later?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.40,0:12:05.11,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I have my own room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.11,0:12:06.46,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.05,0:12:09.53,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I want to see the photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.86,0:12:12.78,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Where was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.78,0:12:14.72,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,In a detached room at our house.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.72,0:12:16.66,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,My grandma found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.27,0:12:20.47,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I don't know why it \Nwas in there, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.47,0:12:21.67,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.67,0:12:26.09,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,My aunt Reiko uses that room.
