Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.37,0:12:38.52,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Can you tell which one \NYomiyama Misaki is?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.52,0:12:43.90,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Well, I can see that one \Nperson looks strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.27,0:12:47.50,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Strange? Like how?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.50,0:12:48.90,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Like...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.90,0:12:53.67,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,He's kind of blurry, compared \Nto the others in the photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.67,0:12:55.32,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Distorted, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.32,0:12:56.41,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.41,0:13:00.17,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,What about the color? \NDo you see any strange colors?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.17,0:13:02.47,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.08,0:13:04.67,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.23,0:13:07.50,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Are these other photos \Nalso your mom's?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.50,0:13:08.53,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.07,0:13:11.34,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,They really did look alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.34,0:13:12.68,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.68,0:13:16.65,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Your mother and your aunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.65,0:13:18.02,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.02,0:13:20.81,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Their faces look the \Nsame, even as kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.21,0:13:25.75,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Does Reiko paint at home?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.75,0:13:26.82,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:30.85,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,She considers it her "real" job.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.85,0:13:32.66,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.66,0:13:36.81,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You were drawing something \Ntoo, weren't you? An angel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.81,0:13:39.30,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Who was the model for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.30,0:13:40.73,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It was...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.51,0:13:44.31,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Your cousin Misaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.31,0:13:46.55,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.55,0:13:50.15,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,When we first met, \Nat the hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.78,0:13:56.43,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,were you taking that \Ndoll to your late cousin?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.43,0:13:58.80,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Did you think it was odd?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.80,0:13:59.88,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.88,0:14:03.03,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It's sort of complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.03,0:14:06.54,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I don't really like \Ntalking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.74,0:14:09.33,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Could you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.33,0:14:10.25,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.56,0:14:15.41,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Kirika, my mother's, \Nreal name is Yukiyo,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.83,0:14:18.92,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,and Misaki's mother's \Nname is Mitsuyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.92,0:14:22.43,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,They're twins, almost identical.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.43,0:14:26.13,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,When they grew up, \Nthey both got married,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.13,0:14:28.38,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,and Mitsuyo became a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.78,0:14:30.83,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,To your cousin Misaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.83,0:14:33.41,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,And one other.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.97,0:14:36.72,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,She had twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.72,0:14:37.67,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.67,0:14:40.72,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,One year later, Yukiyo \Nbecame pregnant too,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.73,0:14:44.85,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,but she miscarried.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.37,0:14:46.73,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You mentioned that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.73,0:14:51.90,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Yukiyo was heartbroken. \NShe almost had a break down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.45,0:14:55.19,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,To make matters worse, \Nthe Fujioka household,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.19,0:14:57.03,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,where the twins were born, \Nwas in financial trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.58,0:14:59.83,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,The Misaki household, \Non the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.83,0:15:03.06,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,needed something to \Nsoothe Yukiyo's heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.06,0:15:06.46,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It was a matter of \Nsupply and demand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.46,0:15:07.31,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You mean—?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.31,0:15:09.29,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I was given to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.47,0:15:14.36,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I think they gave me \Nto her, instead of Misaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.36,0:15:16.84,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,because of my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.84,0:15:18.30,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.30,0:15:22.16,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,If the Misakis took \Nin a daughter named Misaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.16,0:15:23.68,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,then her name would \Nbe Misaki Misaki, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.28,0:15:30.99,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I've been raised as Yukiyo—as Kirika's only daughter for as long as I can remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.99,0:15:34.69,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I think I was in fifth \Ngrade when I found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.69,0:15:37.80,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,My grandmother \Naccidentally let it slip.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.80,0:15:41.02,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I'd never seen my \Nmother so flustered.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.02,0:15:44.44,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,She probably planned on keeping it a secret for the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.28,0:15:48.24,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,What happened \Nwhen you found out?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.91,0:15:53.87,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I wanted to meet Fujioka \NMitsuyo, my other mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.87,0:15:57.03,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I told Kirika that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.03,0:16:01.05,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,At first, she looked \Nincredibly sad,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.85,0:16:04.43,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,but then she was furious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.43,0:16:07.57,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,She didn't want you to \Nmeet your birth mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.57,0:16:08.98,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.50,0:16:11.74,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,She doesn't involve \Nherself in my life much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.74,0:16:14.24,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Except for—as I've \Nmentioned—certain things.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.24,0:16:16.11,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Right. I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.99,0:16:19.52,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I think she's anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.52,0:16:24.62,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It's probably the reason why \Nshe has me carry a cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.07,0:16:27.95,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Though, during all that,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.95,0:16:30.13,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I was secretly \Nmeeting with Misaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.59,0:16:35.46,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,By then, she also knew \Nthat we were twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.46,0:16:39.97,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,We felt that we were connected, \Nwhether we wanted to be or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.97,0:16:43.54,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,She would sneak into \Nmy house sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.54,0:16:47.87,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,She said she liked my house because \Nit was filled with pretty dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.38,0:16:53.06,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,When I asked her what she \Nwanted for her birthday in April,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.06,0:16:55.90,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,she said, "I want that doll."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.90,0:17:00.52,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Soon after starting ninth \Ngrade though, she suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.52,0:17:02.28,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,That's what you were doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.28,0:17:05.21,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I had made a promise with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.56,0:17:10.44,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,So you weren't cousins. \NYou were sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.44,0:17:11.29,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.29,0:17:14.92,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,That's why you told me, \N"It may have already begun."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.39,0:17:17.58,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,You remember that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.58,0:17:18.88,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.88,0:17:22.17,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Why didn't you \Ntell me back then?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.88,0:17:24.22,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.20,0:17:26.39,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.11,0:17:29.06,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I didn't want to believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.58,0:17:32.90,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I didn't want to believe \NMisaki had died
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.90,0:17:35.15,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,because of some crazy curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.15,0:17:36.52,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.14,0:17:39.28,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I could only \Ncall her my cousin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.28,0:17:41.28,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I didn't want to say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.54,0:17:49.28,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,The Misaki who died in \NApril was the first victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.28,0:17:51.41,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.41,0:17:57.47,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Everyone else seems to think \Nthe calamity began in May, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.47,0:18:03.38,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,The extra student was already in the \Nclass before I transferred to Yomi North.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.77,0:18:09.45,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Is that why you're so \Ncertain that I'm not dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.45,0:18:10.44,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.44,0:18:13.95,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Because I wasn't in \Nthe class back in April?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.95,0:18:17.64,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,There's that, but it's \Nnot the main reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.37,0:18:20.31,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,What's your main reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.92,0:18:22.74,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.08,0:18:28.95,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,This eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.82,0:18:34.66,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,This doll's eye \Ntells me you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.66,0:18:35.96,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Your left eye?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.96,0:18:40.46,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I think I told you that it lets me see \Nthings that should remain unseen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.46,0:18:43.64,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Yeah. What can it see?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.64,0:18:44.97,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,The...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.12,0:18:48.81,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,...color of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.81,0:18:51.55,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,The color of things \Nclose to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.55,0:18:52.82,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Color?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.82,0:18:54.36,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,What color is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.19,0:19:02.06,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,A color I've never seen \Nwith my right eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.06,0:19:05.89,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It doesn't belong with \Ncolors like red and blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.40,0:19:08.63,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It's unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.63,0:19:13.36,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,And you can only see that \Ncolor in someone who's dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.36,0:19:15.41,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It's clearest in dead people,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.97,0:19:19.37,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,and faint in those with \Nserious illnesses or injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.37,0:19:23.34,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You mean, you can tell \Nwhen people are about to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.10,0:19:28.54,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,You can't understand how I \Ncan see these things, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.54,0:19:30.05,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.05,0:19:33.35,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I've had to accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.35,0:19:38.15,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I've never even talked \Nto Misaki about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.15,0:19:40.30,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,At some point,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.30,0:19:43.55,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I decided to keep this eye \Ncovered for the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.73,0:19:51.78,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,That's why I wanted to see \Nthat photo from 26 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.78,0:19:56.82,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You could see the color of \Ndeath in Yomiyama Misaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.82,0:19:58.46,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.46,0:20:02.90,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It's the first time I've ever seen \Nthat color so clearly in a photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.67,0:20:09.27,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I don't see the \Ncolor of death in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.27,0:20:12.46,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,That's how I \Nknow it's not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.46,0:20:14.02,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,You're not the extra.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.02,0:20:18.26,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,And you know it's not \Nyou for the same reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.68,0:20:25.40,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Does that mean you already \Nknow who the extra person is?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.80,0:20:33.45,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I try to keep my \Neye patch on at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.45,0:20:37.66,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,But you wrote \N"Who is dead?" on your desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.66,0:20:41.00,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I didn't think finding out \Nwould change anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.00,0:20:45.25,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I did wonder, though, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.39,0:20:48.22,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,What about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.54,0:20:54.35,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Is the dead person \Nhere with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.29,0:21:03.61,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,The extra person...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.27,0:21:07.35,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,...is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.62,0:21:12.24,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.13,0:21:15.99,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.34,0:21:20.12,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Sakaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.41,0:21:25.00,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,I think I fucked up!
